column5: we have a 3D printer at work, amazing capabilities .... being able to build a prototype vehicle in 6 weeks , wow  he says that he wont see it being used for mass production in his lifetime but I think certain components for sure ....
Even Canadian Tire carries a 3D printer now. It's made by the folks @ Dremel. T'aint cheap though.  http://www.canadiantire.ca/en/pdp/dremel-3d-idea-builder-0556769p.html#.VQyQHo7F-So

Even Canadian Tire carries a 3D printer now. It's made by the folks @ Dremel. T'aint cheap though.  http://www.canadiantire.ca/en/pdp/dremel-3d-idea-builder-0556769p.html#.VQyQHo7F-So  Considering that in the mid eighties a Commador dot matrix printer costed over $300, that is not a bad price.  Ten years ago I certainly didn't think that I would be able to pick something like that up for $1300.
You guys want to see the next step in 3D printing?  Jaw dropping.  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VTJq9Z5g4Jk
